<main id="main-content">
    <section class="hero pb-8">
      <div class="container">
        <h1 class="hero__title">The 5 changes of AZERTY Global</h1>
        <p class="hero__subtitle">Everything you need to know in 2 minutes.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Compact intro -->
    <section class="section pt-0 guide-intro">
      <div class="container container--narrow">
        <div class="alert alert--info">
          <h2 class="alert__title text-xl">What doesn't change</h2>
          <p class="alert__text">
            The letters <strong>A to Z</strong>, the accented letters (except <kbd>ù</kbd>) and the vast
            majority of symbols stay where they are. The only changes are the five below —
            and every one of them makes typing easier.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- The 5 changes -->
    <section class="section pt-0 guide-change-cards">
      <div class="container container--narrow">
        <!-- 1. Smart Caps Lock -->
        <details class="card mb-4 guide-change" id="1" open>
          <summary class="guide-change__summary">
            <h3 class="guide-change__title">1. Smart Caps Lock</h3>
          </summary>
          <div class="guide-change__content">
            <p class="mb-3 text-secondary">
              With <kbd>Caps Lock</kbd> on, the letters (A-Z) and the accented letters become capitals:
              <kbd>é</kbd> → <strong>É</strong>, <kbd>è</kbd> → <strong>È</strong>, <kbd>à</kbd> → <strong>À</strong>,
              <kbd>ç</kbd> → <strong>Ç</strong>.
            </p>
            <p class="text-secondary">
              Punctuation, numbers and symbols are not affected by Caps Lock — no more surprise digits
              when you only wanted capital letters.
            </p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <!-- 2. Direct period access -->
        <details class="card mb-4 guide-change" id="2">
          <summary class="guide-change__summary">
            <h3 class="guide-change__title">2. Direct period access</h3>
          </summary>
          <div class="guide-change__content">
            <p class="mb-3 text-secondary">
              No more Shift! The period <strong>.</strong> is now in direct access, like on almost every
              keyboard in the world. The semicolon moves to <kbd>Shift</kbd> + <kbd>.</kbd>.
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-muted">
              💡 The period is far more frequent than the semicolon — it deserves direct access.
            </p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <!-- 3. At sign and hash -->
        <details class="card mb-4 guide-change" id="3">
          <summary class="guide-change__summary">
            <h3 class="guide-change__title">3. @ and # on the top-left key</h3>
          </summary>
          <div class="guide-change__content">
            <p class="mb-3 text-secondary">
              The at sign <strong>@</strong> (direct) and the hash <strong>#</strong> (with <kbd>Shift</kbd>) are now
              on the old <kbd>²</kbd> key, left of the <kbd>1</kbd> — just like on the macOS French AZERTY.
            </p>
            <p class="mb-3 text-secondary">
              Typing email addresses has never been easier. For developers, # is also available with
              <kbd>AltGr</kbd> + <kbd>:</kbd>.
            </p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <!-- 4. Programming symbols -->
        <details class="card mb-4 guide-change" id="4">
          <summary class="guide-change__summary">
            <h3 class="guide-change__title">4. Programming symbols on the home row</h3>
          </summary>
          <div class="guide-change__content">
            <p class="mb-3 text-secondary">
              No more finger gymnastics: the programming symbols are grouped on the home row with
              <kbd>AltGr</kbd> — even more accessible than on a US QWERTY:
            </p>
            <p class="mb-3 text-secondary">
              <kbd>{</kbd> <kbd>}</kbd> under the left middle and index fingers (D, F)<br>
              <kbd>\</kbd> <kbd>|</kbd> on the two middle keys (G, H)<br>
              <kbd>[</kbd> <kbd>]</kbd> under the right index and middle fingers (J, K)
            </p>
            <div class="guide-dev-shortcuts mb-3" aria-label="Ergonomic shortcuts for programming symbols">
              <div class="guide-dev-shortcut">
                <kbd>~</kbd>
                <span><kbd>AltGr</kbd> + <kbd>N</kbd></span>
              </div>
              <div class="guide-dev-shortcut">
                <kbd>`</kbd>
                <span><kbd>AltGr</kbd> + <kbd>L</kbd></span>
              </div>
              <div class="guide-dev-shortcut">
                <kbd>^</kbd>
                <span><kbd>AltGr</kbd> + <kbd>I</kbd></span>
              </div>
              <div class="guide-dev-shortcut">
                <kbd>#</kbd>
                <span><kbd>AltGr</kbd> + <kbd>:</kbd></span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </details>

        <!-- 5. International accents -->
        <details class="card mb-4 guide-change" id="5">
          <summary class="guide-change__summary">
            <h3 class="guide-change__title">5. International accents on the ù key</h3>
          </summary>
          <div class="guide-change__content">
            <p class="mb-3 text-secondary">
              The <kbd>ù</kbd> and <kbd>%</kbd> keys moved to make room for two accent dead keys:
            </p>
            <p class="mb-3 text-secondary">
              • <strong>Acute accent ´</strong> — to type á, é, í, ó, ú (Spanish, Hungarian…)<br>
              • <strong>Grave accent `</strong> — to type à, è, ì, ò, ù (Italian, French…)
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-muted">
              💡 ù stays available with <kbd>AltGr</kbd> + <kbd>U</kbd> or <kbd>´</kbd> then <kbd>V</kbd>.
              % is on <kbd>Shift</kbd> + <kbd>)</kbd>.
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm mt-3 text-muted">
              💡 Many more accents are available through the AZERTY Global dead keys — see below.
            </p>
          </div>
        </details>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- French essentials memo -->
    <section class="section pt-0">
      <div class="container container--narrow">
        <h2 class="text-center mb-6 guide-memo-title">📝 French essentials</h2>

        <div class="table-wrapper memo-table" tabindex="0" role="region" aria-label="French essentials with AZERTY Global">
          <table class="table">
            <caption>French essentials with AZERTY Global</caption>
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Character</th>
                <th>Description</th>
                <th>Shortcut</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>É È À Ç</strong></td>
                <td>Accented capitals</td>
                <td><kbd>Caps Lock</kbd> + <kbd>é</kbd> / <kbd>è</kbd> / <kbd>à</kbd> / <kbd>ç</kbd></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>œ Œ</strong></td>
                <td>As in "cœur", "œuf"</td>
                <td><kbd>AltGr</kbd> + <kbd>O</kbd></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>æ Æ</strong></td>
                <td>As in "ex æquo"</td>
                <td><kbd>AltGr</kbd> + <kbd>A</kbd></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>« »</strong></td>
                <td>French quotation marks</td>
                <td><kbd>AltGr</kbd> + <kbd>W</kbd> / <kbd>X</kbd></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong> </strong></td>
                <td>Narrow non-breaking space (before ? ! : ;)</td>
                <td><kbd>AltGr</kbd> + <kbd>Space</kbd></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong> </strong></td>
                <td>Non-breaking space</td>
                <td><kbd>AltGr</kbd> + <kbd>Shift</kbd> + <kbd>Space</kbd></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>–</strong></td>
                <td>En dash</td>
                <td><kbd>AltGr</kbd> + <kbd>T</kbd></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>—</strong></td>
                <td>Em dash</td>
                <td><kbd>AltGr</kbd> + <kbd>Shift</kbd> + <kbd>T</kbd></td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- International accents -->
    <section class="section pt-0">
      <div class="container container--narrow">
        <h2 class="text-center mb-6 guide-memo-title">🌍 International accents</h2>

        <p class="mb-4 text-secondary">
          Dead keys type an accent first, then apply it to the next letter.
          Example: <kbd>´</kbd> then <kbd>A</kbd> → <strong>á</strong>.
        </p>

        <div class="table-wrapper memo-table" tabindex="0" role="region" aria-label="International accents with AZERTY Global">
          <table class="table">
            <caption>International accents with AZERTY Global</caption>
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Accent</th>
                <th>Dead key</th>
                <th>Examples</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>´</strong> acute</td>
                <td>Key right of <kbd>M</kbd></td>
                <td>á í ó ú — Spanish, Hungarian, Czech…</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>`</strong> grave</td>
                <td><kbd>Shift</kbd> + key right of <kbd>M</kbd></td>
                <td>ì ò ù — Italian…</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>~</strong> tilde</td>
                <td><kbd>AltGr</kbd> + key right of <kbd>M</kbd></td>
                <td>ñ ã õ — Spanish, Portuguese…</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>¨</strong> diaeresis / umlaut</td>
                <td><kbd>Shift</kbd> + <kbd>^</kbd> (unchanged)</td>
                <td>ä ö ü — German, Turkish…</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>^</strong> circumflex</td>
                <td><kbd>^</kbd> (unchanged)</td>
                <td>â ê î ô û — French, Portuguese…</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-muted">
          💡 Hundreds of additional letters and symbols are available through dead keys, including ß, ø, å
          and the characters of many African languages (ɛ, ɔ, ŋ…).
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Smooth transition -->
    <section class="section guide-transition">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="text-center mb-6 guide-transition-title">✅ A smooth transition</h2>

        <div class="grid-cols-3 benefits__grid gap-4">
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="card__title"><span class="card__title-icon" aria-hidden="true">⚡</span>Fast learning</h3>
            <p class="card__text">
              A few hours are enough to memorize the main changes.
              The <a href="/images/carte-simplifiee.svg" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">keyboard map</a> helps during the first days.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="card__title"><span class="card__title-icon" aria-hidden="true">⌨️</span>Keep your keyboard</h3>
            <p class="card__text">
              AZERTY Global is software only: your current keyboard works as is, and the letters
              stay exactly where you expect them.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="card__title"><span class="card__title-icon" aria-hidden="true">🔄</span>Reversible anytime</h3>
            <p class="card__text">
              Your original layout is never modified. Turn AZERTY Global off or switch back to the
              standard AZERTY whenever you want.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Final CTA -->
    <section class="section pt-0">
      <div class="container container--narrow text-center">
        <div class="flex-wrap justify-center gap-3 d-flex">
          <button id="open-tester-btn" class="btn btn--success btn--lg" data-track-conversion="try_online" data-track-detail-placement="guide-footer">
            <span>⌨️</span>
            Try it online (in French)
          </button>
          <a href="/en/download" class="btn btn--primary btn--lg" data-track-conversion="download_click" data-track-detail-placement="guide-footer">
            <span>⬇️</span>
            Download for free
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
